collection_notes: 17May2017-Hi Regina and Leslie, Sorry this took me a while. We put material in that cloth filter bag for you in the first three dredges. The first one came up with tons of Chaetopterus tubes. The second (2A) came up with lots of Modiolus shells, and not very much was in the haul so we repeated the dredge (2B) over the same locality but in the reverse direction. I am pretty sure that we didnt add any material from the fourth (called dredge 3) and fifth (called dredge 4) dredges, on the other side of Catalina, which didnt come up with much. Unfortunately, the coordinates we had targeted from historical records did not seem to be in very rocky areas. I have much more detailed start and stop coordinates for the dredges but maybe you are like me and would prefer to only enter a single locality. I used Excel to calculate an average lat/long and depth for the first (CiA) dredge, and the second and third together (CiB), as follows:. 5/4/17. CiA     Santa Catalina Island, Los Angeles Co., CA, dredge 1 of 4, May 4, 2017  33      27.381  -118    30.185  53m. CiB     Santa Catalina Island, Los Angeles Co., CA, dredge 2 (2A and 2B) of 4 (averaged) May 4, 2017    33      27.991  -118    36.325  33m. Collectors: D. Eernisse and S. Wiedrick. Best wishes,. Doug. MBPC: DISCO Collection ID RW17.015
